 but a GM/Guide simply cannot do anything... their hands being tied by Verant's rules.<br>
<br>
So here is my idea...<br>
<br>
A lot of the things GM's can do, players can do. So why not create a flag /volunteer? These people who turn the /volunteer flag on declare themselves &quot;available&quot; to help other players. My vision is that the /volunteer flag would only show up to guides and GMs. Players would not be able to see them. When a GM or Guide cannot help a player, they can check the /volunteer and ask one of those folks if they can help. If the volunteer asked is able to respond and makes an attempt to help they get &quot;a point&quot;. Perhaps their account can be marked or something, like the &quot;soul brand&quot; or whatever you get when you do something bad. After &quot;x&quot; number of points, maybe the volunteer gets a free month of EQ or something. I dunno, some sort of bonus that wouldnt nessecarily have to be an item. Maybe the points can be tracked so you can &quot;turn them in&quot;. 30 points = 1 free month, 100 points = a free expansion, 1000 points = a free trip to a fanfaire. That sort of thing.<br>
<br>
I know there would probably need to be a big waiver (like the one you see with /follow) and maybe even a level limit. This is all just brainstorming before I send off a letter to developers corner. Any feedback or thoughts?<br>
